{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.27",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 27,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 27",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 27 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.27.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:1",
      "text": "Moreover Job continued his parable, and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.27.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:2",
      "text": "As God liveth, who hath taken away my judgment; and the Almighty, who hath vexed my soul;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.27.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:3",
      "text": "All the while my breath is in me, and the spirit of God is in my nostrils;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.27.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:4",
      "text": "My lips shall not speak wickedness, nor my tongue utter deceit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.27.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:5",
      "text": "God forbid that I should justify you: till I die I will not remove mine integrity from me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.27.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:6",
      "text": "My righteousness I hold fast, and will not let it go: my heart shall not reproach me so long as I live.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.27.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:7",
      "text": "Let mine enemy be as the wicked, and he that riseth up against me as the unrighteous.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.27.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:8",
      "text": "For what is the hope of the hypocrite, though he hath gained, when God taketh away his soul?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.27.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:9",
      "text": "Will God hear his cry when trouble cometh upon him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.27.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:10",
      "text": "Will he delight himself in the Almighty? will he always call upon God?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.27.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:11",
      "text": "I will teach you by the hand of God: that which is with the Almighty will I not conceal.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.27.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:12",
      "text": "Behold, all ye yourselves have seen it; why then are ye thus altogether vain?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.27.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:13",
      "text": "This is the portion of a wicked man with God, and the heritage of oppressors, which they shall receive of the Almighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.27.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:14",
      "text": "If his children be multiplied, it is for the sword: and his offspring shall not be satisfied with bread.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.27.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:15",
      "text": "Those that remain of him shall be buried in death: and his widows shall not weep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.27.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:16",
      "text": "Though he heap up silver as the dust, and prepare raiment as the clay;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.27.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:17",
      "text": "He may prepare it, but the just shall put it on, and the innocent shall divide the silver.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.27.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:18",
      "text": "He buildeth his house as a moth, and as a booth that the keeper maketh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.27.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:19",
      "text": "The rich man shall lie down, but he shall not be gathered: he openeth his eyes, and he is not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.27.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:20",
      "text": "Terrors take hold on him as waters, a tempest stealeth him away in the night.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.27.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:21",
      "text": "The east wind carrieth him away, and he departeth: and as a storm hurleth him out of his place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.27.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:22",
      "text": "For God shall cast upon him, and not spare: he would fain flee out of his hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.27.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:23",
      "text": "Men shall clap their hands at him, and shall hiss him out of his place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
